V{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2015}}\u000a{{Use British English|date=January 2015}}\u000a'''Peter Goldie''' (5 November 1946 \u2013 22 October 2011) was a British academic philosopher with interests in ethics and aesthetics. He was the Samuel Hall Chair in Philosophy and Head of the [http://www.socialsciences.manchester.ac.uk/philosophy/ Philosophy Discipline Area] of the [http://www.socialsciences.man.ac.uk/school/ School of Social Sciences] at [[University of Manchester]]. He was educated at [[Felsted School|Felsted]].\u000a\u000aAfter a 25-year career in business in the City of London, culminating as chief executive at the ill-fated [[British and Commonwealth Holdings|British & Commonwealth]], Goldie turned to Philosophy, in 1990.<ref>[http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/obituaries/culture-obituaries/books-obituaries/8853815/Professor-Peter-Goldie.html Obituary in the Telegraph]</ref> He studied at [[University College London]] for a [[Bachelor of Arts|BA]] degree and at [[Balliol College, Oxford]] for a [[Bachelor of Philosophy|BPhil]] followed by a [[Doctor of Philosophy|DPhil]], supervised by [[Bernard Williams]], on emotion, mood and character. Following this, he was a lecturer at [[Magdalen College, Oxford]], for two years and [[King's College London]] before becoming a professor at Manchester in 2005.\u000a\u000aPeter Goldie died on 22 October 2011.<ref>[http://leiterreports.typepad.com/blog/2011/10/in-memoriam-peter-goldie-1946-2011.html In Memoriam: Peter Goldie (1946-2011)]</ref>\u000a\u000a== Books ==\u000a*[http://www.routledge.com/books/details/9780415422826/ Who's Afraid of Conceptual Art, by Peter Goldie and Elisabeth Schellekens, Routledge, 2009]\u000a*[http://www.amazon.com/dp/0199285551 Philosophy and Conceptual Art, edited by Peter Goldie and Elisabeth Schellekens, Oxford University Press, 2007]\u000a*[http://www.amazon.com/dp/0415305144 On Personality, London, Routledge, 2004]\u000a*[http://www.ashgate.com/default.aspx?page=637&calctitle=1&pageSubject=623&sort=pubdate&forthcoming=1&pagecount=12&lang=cy-gb&title_id=4&edition_id=11 Understanding Emotions: Mind and Morals, Ashgate, 2002]\u000a*[http://www.amazon.com/dp/0198238916 The Emotions: A Philosophical Exploration, Oxford: Clarendon Press, 2000]\u000a*[http://www.amazon.co.uk/Mess-Inside-Narrative-Emotion-Mind/dp/0199230730 The Mess Inside: Narrative, Emotion, and the Mind, by Peter Goldie , OUP Oxford, 28 Jun 2012]\u000a\u000a== References ==\u000a*[http://www.ukwhoswho.com/view/article/oupww/whowaswho/U17383 GOLDIE, Prof. Peter Lawrence], ''Who Was Who'', A & C Black, 1920\u20132015; online edn, Oxford University Press, 2014\u000a{{reflist}}\u000a\u000a{{Authority control}}\u000a{{DEFAULTSORT:Goldie, Peter Lawrence}}\u000a[[Category:Academics of King's College London]]\u000a[[Category:Academics of the University of Manchester]]\u000a[[Category:British ethicists]]\u000a[[Category:People educated at Felsted School]]\u000a[[Category:Alumni of University College London]]\u000a[[Category:Alumni of Balliol College, Oxford]]\u000a[[Category:1946 births]]\u000a[[Category:2011 deaths]]\u000a\u000a{{UK-philosopher-stub}}
